replies.body:
LOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOL the only "science" involved w/ {{champion:86}} is timing on pressing your W.  

{{champion:14}} {{champion:22}} {{champion:1}}  All have more skill involved, {{champion:22}} {{champion:1}}  {{champion:14}}  all have skillshot ults that need to be hit to get max value out of the champ, {{champion:14}} you have to hit your E to set up your Q as well as early activating W for the shield explosion damage, {{champion:22}}  hawkshot requires macro knowledge, and last hitting w/ {{champion:1}}  q makes you learn your damage to minions.  


{{champion:86}}  as said, only has to worry about the timing on W.  By far the simplest champ to play, when i want to turn my brain off for a game (usually after a tilting game or a bunch of games) I play {{champion:86}}
